        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 4:59PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ridgewood, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ridgewood, Nanuet, Tappan, Pearl River, Norwood, Orangeburg,
Westwood, Hillsdale, River Vale, Waldwick, Washington Township, Park
Ridge, Closter, Chestnut Ridge, and Montvale.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
